messages.message: +1 to this. While adding lots of fields in one go is great for demos, for anything but the most simple use case, we need a complex prompt to find the data as we need to provide more context. At the moment the current UI for this makes you wait quite a long time before you can go in and edit the fields, and its not very discoverable that you can go in and edit
This message is sort of releated and shows reasons why often we need to use complex prompts to extract. https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0516UPPMT3/p1698312308233009
